==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inwards
<hw>In"wards</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>inweard</ets>. The ending
<it>-s</it> is prop. a genitive ending. See <er>Inward</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>, <er>-wards</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Toward the inside; toward the center or interior;
<as>as, to bend a thing <ex>inward</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Into, or toward, the mind or thoughts; inwardly;
<as>as, to turn the attention <ex>inward</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So much the rather, thou Celestial Light,⟦br⟧
Shine <qex>inward</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inwardly</ent>⟦br⟧

